data.name: 0xmusic
data.description:
0xmusic is a collection of generative audiovisual DJs - which are called 0xDJs. Each 0xDJ can create an infinite number of music pieces in real time. All code is stored on the Ethereum blockchain.

When the Play button is touched, a brand new song is created, and the image comes alive. The song will continue playing until you either hit Play again or the DJ moves to the next track. At this time, all memory of the prior piece is destroyed, and the new song is created. This march of creation and destruction will continue as long as 0xmusic exists on the blockchain. In this sense, each piece is both eternal and ephemeral, living in a state of superposition until it is â€˜observedâ€™.

All NFTs are CC0.

Prime numbers are closely related to cryptography. This artwork record the scientists, cypherpunks, opinion leaders and other figures who have made an impact on the 21st century. All the NFTs have been minted during Devcon5 in Oct 2019

data.name: 21 Heads - Portraits of Crypto Pioneers
data.description:
This is a series of digital portraits of famous pioneers of the cryptocurrency world, created by the artist Max Cryptohead.

Each of these artworks comes in a limited edition of 21 copies. The price per copy is 0.021 Bitcoin, payable in several major cryptocurrencies. When you buy an artwork, you will receive an NFT token which proves your ownership.

The format of each painting is 21 by 21 inches, with a resolution of 300 dpi. This high resolution allows you to print it out on canvas in a digital print store near you.

Printed out on canvas these paintings fit well into your office or living room, so you can show that you belong to the crypto community.

You find more information here: [21heads.com] (https://21heads.com)

data.name: 22 Pigeons
data.description:
Roe Ethridge and [Zome.art](https://zome.art) present *22 Pigeons*, a collection of twenty-two new works derived from Ethridgeâ€™s iconic series of flying pigeons. To create these original works, Ethridge scanned and combined his analogue pigeon photographs from the early 2000s, resulting in a collection of visually dynamic digital collages.

Roe Ethridge is a leading figure in contemporary photography today, with a broad exhibition history that includes elite institutions such as The Museum of Modern Art and The Whitney Museum of American Art. His work has been published extensively, both in numerous monographs and in high end magazines. Ethridgeâ€™s style and practice has influenced a generation of photographers, and he continues to push the boundaries of the medium with his exhibitions, books, magazine work, and now NFTs.

data.name: 36FUJI Art
data.description:
36 BLOCKS OF FUJI is a project with the aim of "sharing a new Japanese culture of Reiwa to the world" through the co-creation of a single NFT by 36 Japanese artists.

This project takes as its motif Katsushika Hokusai's famous work, Fugaku Sanju-Rokkei Kanagawa-oki Namiura (Thirty-six Views of Mount Fuji), and divides it into 36 pieces (6x6), with 36 artists working on each part. In the end, the artists added their own unique expressions to make such a creative artwork.

This AI engine was fed genesis word(s) and a single ungodly image then run for 777 iterations at an average run time of 210 minutes per image in order to dream up a unique 1/1 art piece with that seed image. 

**777 Deadly Sins are stored on the Ethereum blockchain as ERC-721 tokens. **

**Mint at https://opensea.io/collection/mint-sins**
The Seven Deadly Sins NFT collection comes with three unique series which narrates the path on the Journey to Light collection.

data.description: 81 Horizons is a collection of 81 fully on-chain landscapes by artist [Rafael Rozendaal](https://www.newrafael.com/nft/). Each work consists of a unique combination of two coloured rectangles, hand picked by the artist. Released by [Upstream Gallery](https://www.upstreamgallery.nl/), smart contract programming by [Alberto Granzotto](https://twitter.com/vrde), produced by [left gallery](https://left.gallery/).
